Ivy League Exam Analysis

Bugame Gift

1 .Introduction

Analysis of the Ivy League Exam done by Standard 8 pupils at Ebulako Primary School in 2023. The students are divided into 3 streams namely Atlanta, Indianna and Pacifica. Each of the students sat 5 exams for the 5 compulsory subjects offered at the Primary school level. They are English, Kiswahili, Mathematics, Science and SSRE. (Social Studies and Religious Education) Each subject is marked out of 100 marks, therefore the maximum total mark a student can attain is 500 marks. A total of 179 students sat the exam and had their marks recorded and analysed below.

2. Class performance per subject

a. English

Distribution

The table below shows the percentage distribution of marks in English.

2 0 4 15 22 24 24 12 0 0

A majority of the students in Atlanta attained a score ranging from 51 to 70.

Density function

Atlanta’s English scores have a kurtosis value of 3.19 and a skewness value of -0.59. This implies that the distribution is leptokurtic and is skewed negatively about the mean.
